@chapter Introduction

@url{http://tinypoker.org/,TinyPoker} is a collection of poker software
written by @url{http://www.tomcort.com/,Thomas Cort}.
Originally the software was written as part of a poker bot programming competition
held by the @url{http://j9.ubishops.ca/,Computer Science Club} at
@url{http://www.ubishops.ca/,Bishop's University} in Lennoxville,
Quebec, Canada. It has evolved since then and is currently undergoing a
major re-write that will include support for the
@cindex Internet Poker Protocol
Internet Poker Protocol (IPP) version 2.0 and a number of new features.
The TinyPoker project maintains the following components:
@itemize @bullet
@item
@cindex libtinypoker
libtinypoker (development library)

@item
@cindex tinypokerd
tinypokerd (server)

@item
